Controversial media personality, Daddy Freeze has said the devil should not be blamed for destroying marriages. Daddy Freeze said this while reacting to a post by reality television star, Ka3na who blamed the devil for destroying marriages lately. According to her, everyone should remain unmarried since the devil is working overtime and using his influence to destroy marriages. But, Daddy Freeze, reacting said broken marriages are a result of shortcomings and personal errors not the devil. According to him, the devil did not destroy any marriage in the Bible so Christians should stop the blame game. His post read: “Dear K3na and Nigerian Christians. The devil does not destroy marriages; the devil did not destroy a single marriage in the entire Bible, read for yourself to verify. “So please, let us stop blaming the devil for our personal errors and shortcomings.” Celebrity marriages have been experiencing crises lately which has stirred reactions online. In March, Justin Dean and Korra Obidi announced plans to divorce over alleged manipulation and narcissistic behaviour after they welcomed their second child. In less than 24hours, Nkechi Blessing’s marriage to her husband, Opeyemi Falegan, also crashed as the husband declared he can no longer be associated with a ‘lesbian’ Nkechi Blessing has since taken to social media to reveal secrets accusing her ex of not being good in bed among other things.